The Boyanska reka (Bulgarian: Боянска река, "Boyana river") is a river in western Bulgaria, a tributary to Vladayska River. The river flows from the northern slopes of highest peak of Vitosha Mountain - Cherni Vrah, crossing Torfeno Branishte Nature Reserve; at the northern foothills of Vitosha the river drops forming the gorgeous Boyana waterfall.
